ERROR: argument 1 must be -inB | -inD | -inH
usage:
convert IN OUT SIZE NUMBER
  IN:
    -inB  NUMBER is binary.
    -inD  NUMBER is decimal.
    -inH  NUMBER is hexadecimal.

  OUT:
    -outB Output will be in binary.
    -outD Output will be in decimal.
    -outH Output will be in hexadecimal.

  SIZE:
    -8    input is an unsigned 8-bit integer.
    -16   input is an unsigned 16-bit integer.
    -32   input is an unsigned 32-bit integer.
    -64   input is an unsigned 64-bit integer.

  NUMBER:
    number to be converted.

